      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-05T23:44:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "About BQ export, here\u0027s the discussion around it: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1C8P0k4BgiQmuCq19wbXeOW0kQlsJJgSrtE8uzNYHqDg/edit?disco\u003dAAAAD_p4ctY",
      "parentUuid": "20bdb777_247e2de2",
      "revId": "09a6136ef2667a5ce910f312f11ec29a90c7edbd",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1c89503b_a8a72704",
        "filename": "resultdb/internal/services/recorder/permissions.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 98,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-05T23:45:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "No need to explicitly check \"project:*\", just checking HasPermission should be enough. Only project:X identities will have the permission.\n\nI want to see how far we can go with just using HasPermission instead of various adhoc checks.",
      "parentUuid": "20bdb777_247e2de2",
      "revId": "09a6136ef2667a5ce910f312f11ec29a90c7edbd",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "18e4eb91_95880d8d",
        "filename": "resultdb/internal/services/recorder/permissions.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 98,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-05T23:50:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Re BQ export: thanks.\n\nLooks like we need \"resultdb.invocations.exportToBigQuery\" permission and I think it should not have any special restrictions. Why would it be bad if project owners (if they really want to) grant this permission to some service account (if they create invocations not through Buildbucket)? E.g. why do we think only Buildbucket will need it?",
      "parentUuid": "1c89503b_a8a72704",
      "revId": "09a6136ef2667a5ce910f312f11ec29a90c7edbd",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "36943ba6_6235b7b9",
        "filename": "resultdb/internal/services/recorder/permissions.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 98,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118104
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-06T01:27:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The reasoning is that anybody who has exportToBigQuery permissions can make resultdb write to any bq table that resultdb has permission to write to, unless we keep track of which realms are authorized to be exported to which table, which seems to exceed the scope of realms.\n\nre: internal roles: how do we make sure that the permission inside the internal role is not granted through some custom role for example?",
      "parentUuid": "18e4eb91_95880d8d",
      "revId": "09a6136ef2667a5ce910f312f11ec29a90c7edbd",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c090699d_444bd46d",
        "filename": "resultdb/internal/services/recorder/permissions.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 98,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-06T17:51:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e can make resultdb write to any bq table that resultdb has permission to write to\n\nnot exactly. ResultDB uses a project-scoped service account, so it is \"write to any bq table that the LUCI project has permission to write to\". Our job here is to ensure that the instruction \"please export to this table\" are coming from a place that the LUCI project trusts. It is secure for buildbucket because buildbucket reads destination tables from project-level configs. But it is not secure for invocations created by individual developers who intent to just upload test results to ResultDB (without BQ).",
      "parentUuid": "36943ba6_6235b7b9",
      "revId": "09a6136ef2667a5ce910f312f11ec29a90c7edbd",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "767d3c3b_a7536100",
        "filename": "resultdb/internal/services/recorder/permissions.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 98,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-06T19:33:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e But it is not secure for invocations created by individual developers who intent to just upload test results to ResultDB (without BQ).\n\nWhy is it not secure? If a person is granted exportToBigQuery in realms.cfg (a place that \"LUCI project trusts\"), then this person is trusted to export things to whatever BQ table they want. Why do we want to additionally restrict BQ destinations in this case?\n\nRe: internal roles + custom roles. Yeah, good observation. I guess we\u0027ll need internal permissions too.",
      "parentUuid": "c090699d_444bd46d",
      "revId": "09a6136ef2667a5ce910f312f11ec29a90c7edbd",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7cdcb9bb_76caa29e",
        "filename": "resultdb/internal/services/recorder/permissions.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 98,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-06T22:32:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i could be more clear. There is no call for action. I was thinking about the following case:\n1. Suppose we want non-googler (untrusted) Chromium devs to have an option to upload their results to resultdb, so they they can view them nicely \u003d\u003e they must have \"create invocation\" permission.\n2. *If* we also want to analyze their results in BQ, then they should have \"export BQ\" permission.\n3. Problem: they can specify arbitrary table that the project account has access to.\n\nI think our current security model does not support (2) (and that\u0027s OK). Realm-scoped service accounts would make it possible: non-googlers would use a separate restricted realm.",
      "parentUuid": "767d3c3b_a7536100",
      "revId": "09a6136ef2667a5ce910f312f11ec29a90c7edbd",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
